Architecture plan for Issue #103: Add a site favicon

Current structure:
- frontend/: Vite React SPA with index.html as the HTML shell and src/ for app code/styles.
- frontend/public/: Vite static assets copied verbatim to the production site root.
- backend/: Rust Axum server that serves /api routes plus the built frontend/dist static assets.
- shared/: TypeScript DTO/constants package shared by frontend code.

Issue dependency plan:
- Issue #103 is independent. It only touches the frontend static asset pipeline.
- No backend, database, API, or shared DTO changes are required.

Design decisions:
- Add the favicon as frontend/public/favicon.svg so Vite copies it to /favicon.svg during build.
- Reference it in frontend/index.html with <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />.
- Match TLHN branding from PRODUCT.md: dark cyber/glitch aesthetic, red neon TLHN mark, compact rounded tile.
- Keep the SVG static and self-contained; no runtime dependencies or generated assets.

Validation:
- Run npm run build to confirm Vite includes the public asset path and HTML remains valid.
- Optionally curl /favicon.svg after deploy to confirm static serving through the Rust backend.
